    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_azar" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:id="form_d2824e66" type="lemma"><orth>azar</orth></form>
                <sense xml:id="sense_d2824e69"><sense xml:id="sense_d2824e70"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>terror</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>terror</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2824e79"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>ужас</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>horror</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2824e88"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>страх</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>fear</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2824e97"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>напасть</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>misfortune</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense xml:id="sense_d2824e106"><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>беда</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>trouble</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re xml:id="re_d2824e116">
                    <form xml:id="form_d2824e118" type="lemma"><orth>wælazar</orth></form>
                    <sense xml:id="sense_d2824e121"><def xml:lang="ru">id.</def><def xml:lang="en">id.</def></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e130">
                        <quote>dæw rwaǵy mæ cyppar ḱyzǵy fervæztysty zaliag kalmy azaræj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>благодаря тебе мои четыре дочери избавились от страха перед
                                драконом</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>thanks to you my four daughters got rid of their fear of the
                                dragon</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV
                            136</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e149">
                        <quote>Barsægatæ… fæsabyrdær kodtoj sæ azar (Kobetyl)</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Барсаговы ослабили свой террор (над фамилией Кобеевых)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>The Barsagovs have weakened their terror (of the Kobeyev family)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e168">
                        <quote>padcaxy azaræj tarstysty</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>боялись царской кары</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>were of the czar's punishment</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>172</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e187">
                        <quote>adæmæn sæ mast sæxsyst æmæ sæ azar Uldany ʽrdæm fæci</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>у народа закипела ярость, и их террор обрушился на Улдана</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the rage took peopleʼs hearts, and their terror fell upon Uldan</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."/><biblScope>184</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e206" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>ramælʒænæn azaræj, ku fæwwon Cærugtæmæ cud</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>умру от ужаса, если пойду (замуж) к Царуговым</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>I will die of horror if I go (married) to the Tsarugovs</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Gurdž._Æduli"/><biblScope>103</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e229" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>tuxæ, wælazar ibæl make wæd</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пусть не будет над ним ничьей силы и страха</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>let nobodyʼs power and fear be over him</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            169</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e251" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>Mussæ fur azaræj fæqqan æj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Мусса от страха повалился</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Moussa fell down in fear</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 4</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e273" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>tuǧdmæ bacæwuni azaræj…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>страшась пойти в бой…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>fearing to go into battle…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Bes._Ka_ke"/><biblScope>75</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e295" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>azaræj fæǧǧær laston…</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>в страхе я воскликнул…</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>in fear I exclaimed …</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Sam."/><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:id="example_d2824e317">
                        <quote>cy azaræj ærcydystut ūcy ranmæ?</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>от какой беды (проклятия) вы дошли до этого положения?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>from what trouble (curse) did you come to this state?</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>IV
                            80</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Слово иранское (основа <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e339" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>zar-</w>
                        <gloss><q>обижать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e347" xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>огорчать</q></gloss></mentioned> с префиксом <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e353" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>a-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e358" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ā-zar</w></mentioned>, но в осетинском стоит настолько изолированно, что
                    должно быть рассматриваемо как усвоенное из персидского: <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e363" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āzār</w>
                        <gloss><q>обида</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e372" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>огорчение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e378" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>болезнь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e384" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>мука</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e390" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>azar</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e395" xml:lang="ce" extralang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽazar</w></mentioned>. На иранской почве ср. также <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e400" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āzār(ʼʼz’r)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e406" xml:lang="sog"><w>*āzārm(ʼʼzrm)</w>
                        <gloss><q>оскорбление</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e412" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āzār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>оскорблять</q></gloss></mentioned>. Осетинский дает существенное
                    смещение значения.<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note></etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">The word is Iranian (stem<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e426" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>zar-</w>
                        <gloss><q>offend</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e434" xml:lang="ira"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>grieve</q></gloss></mentioned> with prefix<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e440" xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>a-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e445" xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>ā-zar</w></mentioned>, but in Ossetic it is so isolated that it should be
                    considered as learned from Persian:<mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e450" xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>āzār</w>
                        <gloss><q>offense</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e459" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>grief</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e465" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>disease</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e471" xml:lang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>torment</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e477" xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>azar</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e482" xml:lang="ce" extralang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>ʽazar</w></mentioned>. On Iranian ground, cf. also <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e487" xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*āzār(ʼʼz’r)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e493" xml:lang="sog"><w>*āzārm(ʼʼzrm)</w>
                        <gloss><q>insult</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:id="mentioned_d2824e499" xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>āzār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>offend</q></gloss></mentioned>. The Ossetic exhibits a significant
                    shift in meaning.<note type="footnote" n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note></etym>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="ru" n="1">Трудно согласиться с %sВаilеу%s, который
                    усматривает в %iazar%i гипотетический иранский глагол %i*zar-%i ‘двигаться’
                            (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1956, стр. 57, 6Э</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1956, p. 57,
                            60</biblScope></bibl>). В семантике %iazar%i нет ничего, что указывало
                    бы на ‘движение’.</note>
                <note type="footnote" xml:lang="en" n="1">It is hard to agree with %sВаilеу%s who
                    sees in %iazar%i a hypothetical Iranian verb %i*zar-%i ‘move’ (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1956, стр. 57,
                            6Э</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1956, p. 57,
                        60</biblScope></bibl>). There is nothing in the semantics of %iazar%i to
                    indicate ʽmovementʼ.</note>
            </entry>
